CatDescriptText: One firefighter climbs a ladder toward a smoking window in a three story row house.  Four other firemen wait between the front door and the fire truck.  The fire truck is identified as a Pittsburgh Bureau of Fire Engine Company vehicle.  The numeral may be a 3, 5 or 8. The car in the foreground is mid-1960s design.
TitMainTitle: Fire fighters from Engine Company no. 5 fighting fire in two-story row house
